ZH: 今天的顾客很多，我们忙得不可开交。
EN: There are a lot of customers today, we are very busy.

ZH: 作为一名店员，我们要时刻顾及顾客的需求。
EN: As a shop assistant, we need to always consider the needs of the customers.

ZH: 顾客在商店里找不到他们需要的商品。
EN: The customers couldn't find the items they were looking for in the store.

ZH: 这家餐厅的顾客服务态度非常好，吸引了很多顾客。
EN: The customer service at this restaurant is excellent, attracting many customers.

ZH: 这个咖啡馆的顾客来自各个国家。
EN: The customers at this café come from various countries.

ZH: 请问有什么可以帮助您，尊贵的顾客？
EN: How may I assist you, esteemed customer?

ZH: 为了吸引更多顾客，我们需要提供更好的服务。
EN: In order to attract more customers, we need to provide better service.

ZH: 今天店里的顾客反应很积极。
EN: The customers in the store were very responsive today.

ZH: 这个顾客抱怨他买到的商品质量不好。
EN: This customer complained about the poor quality of the product he bought.

ZH: 请不要向顾客透露我们的促销计划。
EN: Please do not disclose our promotional plans to the customers.

ZH: 作为一名服务员，我们要尽力满足每位顾客的需求。
EN: As a waiter, we must do our best to meet the needs of every customer.

ZH: 这种产品一直备受顾客的欢迎。
EN: This product has always been popular with customers.

ZH: 今天的顾客购买力很强。
EN: The customers today have strong purchasing power.

ZH: 这家超市为顾客提供免费送货服务。
EN: This supermarket provides free delivery services for customers.

ZH: 请不要在顾客面前说粗话。
EN: Please do not use vulgar language in front of customers.

ZH: 服务行业的成功取决于对顾客的满意度。
EN: The success of the service industry depends on customer satisfaction.

ZH: 这家饭店每天都聘请新服务员来照顾顾客。
EN: This restaurant hires new waiters every day to look after the customers.

ZH: 这家商店经常会举办各种促销活动来吸引顾客。
EN: This store often holds various promotional activities to attract customers.

ZH: 这位顾客对我们的服务感到非常满意。
EN: This customer is very satisfied with our service. 

ZH: 不管顾客提出什么要求，我们都要尽量满足。
EN: Whatever requests the customer makes, we must do our best to meet them.
